<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do I need to replace breast implants after a certain number of years?</h3>
<p>Modern breast implants are designed to be long-lasting, but they are not considered lifetime devices. Most implants maintain their integrity for 10 to 20 years. Regular monitoring through MRI scans or ultrasounds is recommended to check for silent ruptures or capsular contracture. Many women choose to replace their implants proactively after 15 to 20 years.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I get pregnant after a tummy tuck? Will it affect my results?</h3>
<p>Yes, you can get pregnant after a tummy tuck. However, pregnancy can stretch the abdominal muscles and skin again, potentially compromising the results of the procedure. Dr. Johar recommends completing your family before undergoing a tummy tuck for the best long-term results.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How can I make my Botox results last longer?</h3>
<p>While the duration of Botox is largely determined by your metabolism, certain lifestyle factors can help extend results. Avoiding excessive sun exposure, maintaining a healthy diet, and using skincare products with peptides may help. Some patients find that regular treatments train the muscles to remain relaxed longer over time.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Will my facelift results look natural as I continue to age?</h3>
<p>Yes, a well-performed facelift ages naturally with you. The procedure repositions tissues and removes excess skin, creating a more youthful baseline. As you continue to age, your face will age naturally from this new position, maintaining a refreshed and natural appearance for many years.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is liposuction a permanent solution for fat removal?</h3>
<p>Liposuction permanently removes fat cells from the treated area, and those cells do not regenerate. However, remaining fat cells in the area can enlarge if significant weight is gained. Maintaining a stable weight through diet and exercise ensures that liposuction results are long-lasting and permanent.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>When should I start considering maintenance procedures?</h3>
<p>Maintenance needs vary by procedure and individual. Botox and filler maintenance typically begins as soon as the effects start to wear off, usually every three to six months. For surgical procedures, maintenance may not be needed for many years. Dr. Johar monitors your results and recommends maintenance treatments at the appropriate time.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Does age affect how long plastic surgery results last?</h3>
<p>Age is a factor in result longevity. Younger patients generally enjoy longer-lasting results due to better skin elasticity and healing capacity. However, patients of all ages can achieve excellent, long-lasting results when procedures are performed by an experienced, board-certified surgeon and maintained with healthy lifestyle habits.</p>
</div>
</div>

